<TEXT>
record temperatures continued to blast northern california on 
sunday as people sought relief from the fifth day of persistent 
heat at crowded beaches seaside boardwalks and inland waterways 
its like a summer day its not typical of this time of the 
year at all said jamie bolt at the bethel island harbor about 
50 miles east of san francisco 
parched southern california got a breath of fresh air however 
when coastal breezes sent temperatures plunging more than 15 
degrees in many areas ending the hottest april week on record 
the high at the los angeles civic center was 76 degrees late in 
the afternoon a sharp drop from saturdays 91 and thursdays 106 
a record high for an april day 
the national weather service has predicted a cooling trend for 
the heat wave that has broken historic levels throughout most of 
the region over the weekend 
but on sunday san francisco logged a high of 91 tying its 
alltime streak of four consecutive days in which the thermometer 
hit or exceeded 90 degrees similar stretches were recorded in 
september 1904 and september 1939 
sundays high also broke the citys record set last year of 85 
for the date 
sacramentos high of 95 was also a record for the date and 
marked the fourth straight day of 90orabove temperatures 
bakersfield sweated through 97 degrees four degrees higher than 
its yearold record of 93 for april 9 other cities with record 
highs were fresno stockton and san jose at 95 santa rosa at 91 
and alameda at 86 
a high pressure ridge was predicted by the weather service to 
move into the pacific northwest bringing cooler weather and 
temperatures about 10 degrees lower on monday 
</TEXT>
