<TEXT>
a mild earthquake an aftershock of a 
larger quake last monday rattled windows but caused no reported 
damage in northern california on sunday 
the us geological survey said the quake hit at 158 pm 
registering 34 on the richter scale the epicenter on the 
calaveras fault seven miles east of milpitas was almost exactly 
the same as mondays quake measuring 49 the usgs said milpitas 
is about 30 miles south of san francisco 
the openended richter scale measures the energy released by an 
earthquake by tabulating ground motion 
each increase of one number as in a rise from 35 to 45 means 
the ground motion is 10 times greater a 35 earthquake can cause 
slight damage in populated areas 
