<TEXT>
west palm beach fla a 17yearold boy has been convicted of 
killing another teenager and injuring six others by driving into a 
crowd of partying classmates 
eric norstrom sank into his chair shaking and stunned when he 
was found guilty friday of vehicular homicide reckless driving and 
two counts of culpable negligence to end the weeklong trial 
nobody won said raymond hamby whose son charles 19 
remains in a traumatic brain injury center in central florida as a 
result of the accident 
norstrom was speeding to the party in boynton beach on march 24 
1988 when he lost control of his car skidded out of control and 
slammed into the crowd killing amber hunter 16 
defense attorney michael salnick maintained the crash was an 
accident not a crime it was a horrible thing for everybody 
he said eric is very very sorry for what happened 
but salnick said sending the teenager to prison because of the 
accident would mean another life being wasted as a result of this 
whole horrible tragedy 
maria feldman 16 a former cheerleader whose left thigh and 
cheekbone were fractured in the accident said she was satisfied 
with the verdicts 
its not like i got some great satisfaction because hes going 
to be in prison feldman said i feel bad but i didnt do 
anything wrong 
palm beach county circuit judge marvin mounts agreed to postpone 
sentencing until after norstrom graduates june 7 state sentencing 
guidelines recommend three to seven years in prison for the 
convictions 
