<TEXT>
syrian gunners on saturday fired shells 
into lebanons christian enclave in defiance of a ceasefire called 
by the arab league but no casualties were reported 
a police spokesman said syrian artillery emplacements fired five 
howitzer shells into different areas of the 310squaremile 
enclave the 130millimeter shells exploded in unpopulated areas 
said the spokesman who cannot be named in line with standing rules 
he said gunners of gen michel aouns 20000 christian troops 
did not respond to the syrian fire 
its what we call artillery harassment its a message that 
says there is no settlement yet and there is no total war the 
spokesman said 
the truce was called wednesday by kuwaits foreign minister 
sheik sabah alahmed alsabah who heads an arab league committee 
on lebanon 
despite the relative calm that had prevailed since early friday 
the divided capital seemed a ghost city 
most civilians stayed indoors out of fear of renewed shelling 
duels 
the current fighting erupted march 8 after aoun ordered a 
blockade of militiarun ports which deprive the government of an 
estimated 100 million annually in lost taxes 
druse warlord walid jumblatts progressive socialist party 
militia responded by shelling the christian enclave and syrian 
troops later joined jumblatt in the confrontation 
the fighting has left 177 people dead and 591 wounded 
jumblatt told a news conference in damascus the syrian capital 
that there was no possibility of a political dialogue with aoun to 
settle lebanons problems 
what is the use of a dialogue with these people who 
perpetrated the catastrophe there will be no dialogue with aoun 
and his clique jumblatt said 
aoun and other christian leaders accuse the syrians of siding 
with the moslems in lebanons 14yearold civil war and failing to 
respect their 1976 peacekeeping mandate from the arab league syria 
has 40000 troops in lebanon 
jumblatt repeated syrian denials of involvement in the fighting 
and also accused aoun of seeking to impose his solution with 
massive imports of material and political support from iraq 
iraq and syria ruled by rival wings of the baath socialist 
party have been at odds for a decade syria supported persian iran 
against arab iraq in the eightyear gulf war suspended by a united 
nations ceasefire on aug 20 
the syrian news agency reported that syrian foreign minister 
farouk alsharaa discussed the situation in lebanon with soviet 
foreign ministry representative jinadi trasov who is visiting 
damascus 
syria keeps close relations with the soviet union its major 
arms supplier 
a commentary on damascus radio reiterated the syrian position of 
seeking to create an ambiance that will secure stability and 
tranquillity in lebanon for the lebanese people 
